  "text": "C ell cycle regulation balances the requirement of proliferation during tissue growth and homeostasis, with the need to ensure that damaged DNA is not propagated to future generations. Checkpoints have evolved to achieve control of cell cycle progression in response to DNA damage. The importance of DNA damage checkpoints is highlighted by the fact that their dysregulation is the fundamental basis of oncogenesis [CITATION_1] .",
